# Frontend Guidelines & Rules

## Forms & Monetary Inputs (Float / Currency)
**CRITICAL RULE**: Whenever dealing with float values, monetary values, prices, discounts, or credit limits in frontend forms, **ALWAYS** use the `<CurrencyInput />` component located at `src/components/CurrencyInput.tsx`.

### Why?
The `CurrencyInput` component handles input masking, formatting (e.g. `1.000,90`), and locale-specific conversions perfectly, ensuring consistent user experience and avoiding backend parsing errors associated with raw float inputs.

### Usage
```tsx
import { CurrencyInput } from '@/components/CurrencyInput';

// Price / Money
<CurrencyInput 
  prefixStr="R$ "
  value={product.price} 
  onChangeValue={(val) => setProduct({...product, price: val})} 
/>

// Percentages
<CurrencyInput 
  suffixStr="%"
  value={customer.discount} 
  onChangeValue={(val) => setCustomer({...customer, discount: val})} 
/>
```

Do not use `<input type="number" />` for monetary or percentage values.
